						<!-- firstHeading -->
			<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en"><span dir="auto">Brethren of Purity</span></h1>
			<!-- /firstHeading -->
			<!-- bodyContent -->
			<div id="bodyContent">
								<!-- tagline -->
				<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
				<!-- /tagline -->
								<!-- subtitle -->
				<div id="contentSub"></div>
				<!-- /subtitle -->
																<!-- jumpto -->
				<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<!-- /jumpto -->
								<!-- bodycontent -->
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Irakischer_Maler_von_1287_001.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bf/Irakischer_Maler_von_1287_001.jpg/220px-Irakischer_Maler_von_1287_001.jpg" width="220" height="293" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bf/Irakischer_Maler_von_1287_001.jpg/330px-Irakischer_Maler_von_1287_001.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bf/Irakischer_Maler_von_1287_001.jpg/440px-Irakischer_Maler_von_1287_001.jpg 2x" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Irakischer_Maler_von_1287_001.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf7/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
<a href="Persian_language" title="Persian language">Persian</a> <a href="Illuminated_manuscript" title="Illuminated manuscript">manuscript illumination</a> from the 12th century CE showing the Brethren of Purity.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>The Brethren of Purity</b> (<a href="Persian_language" title="Persian language">Persian</a>: <span lang="fa" xml:lang="fa">اخوان‌الصفا</span>‎ <span title="Persian transliteration" class="Unicode" style="white-space:normal; text-decoration: none"><i>akhvãn alsfã</i></span>; also <b>The Brethren of Sincerity</b>) were a <a href="Secret_society" title="Secret society">secret society</a><sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> of <a href="Early_Islamic_philosophy" title="Early Islamic philosophy">Muslim philosophers</a> in <a href="Basra" title="Basra">Basra</a>, <a href="Iraq" title="Iraq">Iraq</a>, in the 10th century CE.</p>
<p>The structure of this mysterious organization and the identities of its members have never been clear.<sup id="cite_ref-brethren-25-seyyed_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-brethren-25-seyyed-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup> Their <a href="Esotericism" title="Esotericism">esoteric</a> teachings and philosophy are expounded in an <a href="Epistolary_novel" title="Epistolary novel">epistolary</a> style in the <i><a href="Encyclopedia_of_the_Brethren_of_Purity" title="Encyclopedia of the Brethren of Purity">Encyclopedia of the Brethren of Purity</a></i> (<i>Rasa'il Ikhwan al-safa'</i>), a giant compendium of 52 epistles that would greatly influence later encyclopedias. A good deal of Muslim and Western scholarship has been spent on just pinning down the identities of the Brethren and the century in which they were active.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc">
